			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How Dare You!?<a name="61922"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 4:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Any bard who can survive his home streets, alleyways, and taverns knows when and how to use a rapier.
<br />

<br />
You don't stick the pointy end against a dragon's hide, nor do you try to penetrate a shield or plated armor.  You slip in the cracks.  You find the eye, the mouth, the ear.
<br />

<br />
If you are fighting a rock, you sheath your weapon and get more creative.
<br />

<br />
And for those worried about looking tough as a bard, what smoke have you been taking?  You've already been prancing around, singing, playing a flute, and strumming your little lute.  It's a little late to be concerned with manliness.
<br />

<br />
I'll offer one thing though.  The pansy bard will always have a woman in his bed.  They love the song, the dance.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
