				<td colspan="2"><span>&lt;Mode=Pendantic&gt;
<br />
The Rapier was never a weapon of war.  It was developed purely as a dueling weapon for Gentlemen.  The thing is utterly useless even in the most skilled hands against an armored opponent with any degree of skill.
<br />

<br />
At the time the Rapier was used, wearing personal body armor had gone out of style due to changes in weapon technology which made the stuff ineffective.
<br />
&lt;/Mode&gt;
<br />

<br />
In a fantasy game, it hardly matters.  You see some really odd looking weapons in the game, things that would *never* function in the real world.
<br />

<br />
I do have one minor problem.  Bards are a Plate class.  Running around in Plate armor with a Rapier is just silly.</span></td>
